{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}} {{Infobox company | name = '''''Wine-Searcher''''' | logo = Wine-Searcher-Logo.gif | type = Web Search Engine | industry = Internet | products = Wine Information | founder = <!---Martin Brown---> | foundation = 1998 | location = [[Auckland]], New Zealand | homepage = [http://www.wine-searcher.com/ www.wine-searcher.com] }}
'''Wine-Searcher''' is a [[web search engine]] enabling users to locate the price and availability of a given wine, spirit or beer globally, and be directed to a retail outlet selling the alcoholic beverage. As of April 2018, Wine-Searcher had 8.6 million wine listings from 90,952 outlets globally. The site also includes an encyclopedia of wine regions, grape varieties and wine producers.
== History == The company was founded in 1998 by Martin Brown, a former [[e-commerce]] manager for London wine merchant [[Berry Brothers & Rudd|Berry Bros & Rudd]]. In 2006, the operation was shifted from London to Auckland, in Brown's native [[New Zealand]]. The company now has a staff of roughly 65 employees including [[Developer (software)|software developers]], database administrators, account managers, wine experts and writers.
== Products and services == Wine-Searcher collects online wine lists from a range of wine retailers, producers and auction houses. A team of wine experts vets the listings, which are uploaded to a database. Merchants can choose to boost their own listings by paying a yearly fee to "sponsor" Wine-Searcher. These listings are available to all users, but for a small fee, an upgrade to Pro Version will return all results.
Apart from its core function as a database, Wine-Searcher also an encyclopedia which covers the most important grape varieties and wine regions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wine-searcher.com/regions.lml |title=Wine Regions & Appellations |accessdate=11 February 2014}}</ref> It also provides daily wine news . Wine-Searcher has mobile apps for iOS and Android.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wine-searcher.com/app.lml |title=Wine-Searcher Mobile App |accessdate=17 February 2014}}</ref>
Wine-Searcher's income derives from charging subscribers for "pro version" access, charging retailers to share their listings, data and advertisements on the website.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wine-pages.com/ubb/ultimatebb.php?ubb=get_topic;f=1;t=041462l |title=Wine Searcher |accessdate=27 September 2014}}</ref>
== Reviews == Over the years, Wine-Searcher's contribution to [[online]] wine business has been recognized by numerous sources. Notable among them are ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref name="New York Times">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/12/dining/why-cant-you-find-that-wine.html?iid=chix-sphere |title=Why Can't You Find That Wine? |accessdate=12 February 2014 |author= |last=Asimov |first=Eric |date=11 February 2014 |publisher=New York Times.}}</ref> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'',<ref name=Time>{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1580402,00.html?iid=chix-sphere |title=How to Choose the Right Wine |accessdate=15 July 2008 |author= |last=Kapnick |first=Sharon |date=18 January 2007 |publisher=Time Inc.}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine,<ref name=Forbes>{{cite news |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061020164118/http://www.forbes.com/bow/b2c/review.jhtml?id=1372 |archivedate=20 October 2006 |url=https://www.forbes.com/bow/b2c/review.jhtml?id=1372 |title=Website Reviews – Wine-Searcher.com |accessdate=15 July 2008 |author= |publisher=Forbes}}</ref> ''[[Seattle Times]]'',<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.seattletimes.com/life/food-drink/web-site-helps-consumers-find-a-favorite-wine/ |title=Web site helps consumers find a favorite wine |accessdate=15 July 2008 |author= |last=Gregutt |first=Paul |date=21 May 2008 |publisher=The Seattle Times Company}}</ref> [[Jancis Robinson]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jancisrobinson.com/articles/jr789 |title=Comparing wine prices online – who's best |accessdate=15 July 2008 |author= |last=Robinson |first=Jancis |date=16 March 2002 |publisher=Jancis Robinson}}</ref> ''[[The Journal Gazette]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.journalgazette.net/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20071006/FEAT0112/710060396&template=printart |title=Spread word on shipping |accessdate=15 July 2008 |author= |last=Stockman |first=Dan |author2=Krista Stockman |date=6 October 2007 |publisher=The Journal Gazette}}</ref> ''[[Pittsburgh Tribune-Review]]'',<ref name=PTR>{{cite web |url=http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/living/fooddrink/winecellar/s_502039.html |title=Web sites offer entertaining, useful wine information |accessdate=15 July 2008 |author= |last=DeSimone |first=Dave |date=11 April 2007 |publisher=Tribune-Review Publishing Co.}}</ref> ''[[The Times]]'',<ref name="The Times UK">{{cite web |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/food_and_drink/wine/article3146134.ece |title=Don't believe the hype |accessdate=15 July 2008 |author= |last=MacQuitty |first=Jane |date=12 January 2008 |publisher=Times Newspapers Ltd. |location=London}}</ref> "Bloomberg Luxury",<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/luxury |work=Bloomberg |title=Pursuits – Bloomberg Business}}</ref><ref name="Bloomberg Luxury">{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-15/throw-a-great-party-with-wines-under-15.html |title=Throw a Great Party with Wines Under $15 |accessdate=18 December 2013 |author= |last=Mariani |first=John |date=15 September 2013 |publisher=Bloomberg Luxury}}</ref> ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''.<ref name="Los Angeles Times">{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2010/aug/12/food/la-fo-winesearcher-20100812 |title=Wine-searcher.com levels the wine industry playing field |accessdate=10 December 2010 |author= |last=Comiskey |first=Patrick |date=12 August 2010 |publisher=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>
